  "unmapped_findings": [
    "PREP-prepared Fe-30Mn-9Al-C-3Ni powder has a median particle size D50 of 35.69 μm, Hall flowability of 14 s/50 g, and solid particles without hollow structures.",
    "The minimum density among SLM-printed samples is 6.78 g/cm³, which is much lower than that of 304 stainless steel (7.93 g/cm³).",
    "FWHM values of the (111) diffraction peaks for P-70, P-90, P-110, P-130, and P-150 are 0.289, 0.274, 0.263, 0.255, and 0.237 respectively, indicating increasing grain size with increasing laser energy density.",
    "Reduction of area (Z) from Table 2: P-70 25.79%, P-90 35.48%, P-110 35.16%, P-130 34.84%, P-150 32.22%, as-cast 17.10%.",
    "Tensile fracture surfaces: P-70 shows lack of fusion and internal cracks; P-90 and P-110 exhibit dominant ductile dimples; P-130 and P-150 show internal pores, cracks, and balling leading to reduced plasticity.",
    "XRD pattern of PREP powder shows diffraction peaks for both γ-Fe(M) and α-Fe(M) phases, while SLM-printed samples contain only austenite γ-Fe(M) due to rapid cooling suppressing ferrite formation.",
    "Detailed grain-size distributions for all SLM samples are provided in Fig. 8; grain size continuously increases from 8.1 μm (P-70) to 14.3 μm (P-150) in the cross-section.",
    "The side surface of SLM-printed samples was observed to be softer than the top surface in hardness measurements."
  ]
